SIMPLE: monopetalous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monopetalous
<hw>Mon`o*pet"al*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>petal</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>monop⟦eacute⟧tale</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having only
one petal, or the corolla in one piece, or composed of petals cohering
so as to form a tube or bowl; gamopetalous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The most recent authors restrict this form to flowers
having a solitary petal, as in species of <gen>Amorpha</gen>, and use
<contr>gamopetalous</contr> for a corolla of several petals combined
into one piece. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Gamopetalous</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monophanous</ent>⟦br⟧
